## Codebase discoveries (TS SDK, sdks/node, verified)
- FULL agent-OTEL parity in src/genai/: startSession/startTurn/startLLM/startTool/
  startSubagent (functions) + OO startTurn()/startLLM()/etc. Same gen_ai spans to
  the SAME endpoint /agents/otel/v1/traces (provider.ts GENAI_OTLP_PATH). TS DOES
  send a project_id header (Python uses Resource attrs instead).
- init is ASYNC (await it). With entity/project form it does NO network (skips
  defaultEntityName + does not health-check, unlike login()). If init is never
  called, all start* are no-ops (AlwaysOffSampler).
- WEAVE_USE_OTEL_V2 defaults FALSE in TS (OPPOSITE of Python's true). Native
  @openai/agents emits legacy calls unless it's set true; then a
  WeaveOtelTracingProcessor (registered via instrumentOpenAIAgents() or the
  --import=weave/instrument hook) emits agent spans. pi-coding-agent is OTel-only.
- Provider/Anthropic/Google/Realtime TS integrations emit legacy calls only.

## Hints for future agents (verification)
- OFFLINE VERIFY (public path): await weave.init('entity/project',
  {genai:{spanProcessor: new SimpleSpanProcessor(new InMemorySpanExporter())}})
  -> run agent -> await weave.flushOTel() -> exporter.getFinishedSpans(). The
  spanProcessor override bypasses OTLP; dummy WANDB_API_KEY is enough. Proven.
- Module resolution: TS resolves 'weave' from the nearest node_modules, so the
  shipped examples can't self-resolve from .claude/skills. I verified by running
  the EXACT shipped files inside the sdks/node package context (self-reference to
  'weave' via the exports map after `npm run build`; @opentelemetry from
  node_modules). examples/ts/README.md documents running from a project that has
  weave installed.
- Native path proven by the SDK's OWN suite:
  `node_modules/.bin/jest src/__tests__/integrations/openaiAgent.test.ts -t OTEL`
  (5 passed) — exercises weave-otel-tracing-processor.ts. NOTE: must NOT pass
  --selectProjects modern (the file isn't in that project -> whole suite skips);
  run without project selection.
- Env setup used: pnpm install in sdks/node; npm run build (creates dist for
  self-ref); @openai/agents 0.11.4 + zod were installed by pnpm install.

